The paper discusses the development of a self-learning machine for unsupervised hierarchical pattern classification, which involves techniques such as feature extraction, pattern learning, and clustering. These topics are commonly associated with machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Mirroring Neural Networks (MNNs) for automatic data reduction and feature extraction, which are commonly used in neural network research, indicating that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to image classification, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a clustering algorithm, which is a common technique in data science and statistics, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.SD (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
